# Cipher IAM:
    - Support for 'asscociation' between Identity Profiles
    - Identity Profile 'assocaition' represent managerial hierarchy, accountability relationships, cost-and-payroll relationships, etc., 
    - The associations between Identity Profiles should capture relationship-type, effective-from, effective-to, etc.,
    - A Catalog of Relationship Types is configured per domain. Cardinality, Direction, Associaton Policy, etc., are configured per relationship type.
    - A Special association type is 'delegate' (from Delegator to Delegatee)
    - Cipher should capture delegated authority and automatically shrink it when the delegator's authority shrinks.
    - Subject Groups - Modules should be able to create Subject Groups and assign identities to them
    - Access Control Policies - Modules should be able to create Access Control Policies 
    - Access Control Policies could be based on Groups the user is part of in addition to the roles and explicitly assigned privileges; That is, a policy need not declare or register the privileges associated with a user group in Cipher IAM; Cipher IAM will be responsible for enforcing the policies based on the relationships between Identity Profiles.

